A telephone number is structured as $\text{ABC-DEF-GHIJ}$, where each letter represents a different digit. Each segment's digits are arranged in decreasing order. In this configuration:
- $D$, $E$, and $F$ are three consecutive digits (in any order);
- $G$, $H$, $I$, and $J$ are consecutive odd digits;
- $A + B + C = 12$.
Determine the value of $A$.
$\textbf{(A)}\ 5\qquad \textbf{(B)}\ 6\qquad \textbf{(C)}\ 7\qquad \textbf{(D)}\ 8\qquad \textbf{(E)}\ 9$

